Description: Fragment of double handle, one barrel only preserved, from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine very micaceous grey-brown. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and perhaps cluster of grapes symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Agathinos. Unpublished parallel in Athenian Agora.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0142)
